# Video Model Research & Comparison Report

## Executive Summary
For PL Capital's social media video generation, **Wan 2.1** (via Replicate or Fal.ai) is the recommended primary model due to its unique "Visual Text Generation" capability and highly competitive pricing (~$0.04-$0.05/s). **Kling AI** is a strong secondary choice for high-fidelity cinematic motion. **Fal.ai** and **Replicate** are the preferred API platforms, offering flexible pay-as-you-go access to these top models.

## Top Video Models Comparison (Updated Dec 2025)

| Model | Key New Features (v2.6/Gen-4/2.5) | Best Use Case |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Kling AI 2.6** | **Native Audio** (Sound FX + Voice), 1080p, Improved Motion | **All-in-One Viral Reels** (Visuals + Audio in one pass) |
| **Wan 2.5** | **Native 4K**, Built-in Audio, 10s clips | **High-End Financial Explainers** (Crisp text/charts in 4K) |
| **Runway Gen-4** | **Consistent Characters**, Dual-Input (Text+Image), 4K | **Brand Storytelling** (Recurring characters/mascots) |
| **Sora 2** | 12s clips, "Sketch-to-Video", Audio Sync | Rapid Prototyping, Cinematic Ads |
| **Google Veo 3.1** | "Ingredients to Video" (Consistency), 8s clips | Multi-shot narratives with strict brand control |
| **Wan Animate** | Character Replacement / Animation Mode | Animating specific "Financial Advisor" avatars |
| **OmniHuman 1.5** | **"Cognitive Simulation"**, Perfect Lip-Sync, Full Body | **High-End Digital Advisor** (Speaking directly to camera) |

